# Analytics API Specification

## Base URL
```
https://api.analytics.com/v1
```

## Authentication
All API requests require authentication via Bearer token:
```
Authorization: Bearer <your-api-token>
```

## Common Headers
```
Content-Type: application/json
Accept: application/json
```

## Data Models

### Student
```json
{
  "studentId": "string",
  "name": "string", 
}
```
### Question
```json
 {
  "studentId": "string",
  "examId": "string";
  "questionId": "string";
  "questionType": "string";
  "topicId": "string";
  "answer": "string";
  "answerChangeCount": "integer";   // Number of answer changes
  "flagged": "boolean";
}
```
### Exam
```json
 {
  "studentId": "string",
  "examId": "string";
  "totalDuration": "float";         // In seconds
  "flaggedCount": "integer";
  "questions": Question[];
}
```

---

## Endpoints

### 1. Get Student Exam Information

**GET** `/examInfo/{studentId}/{examId}`

Retrieve specific basic information exam of a student.

#### Query Parameters
| Parameter | Type | Required | Description |
|-----------|------|----------|-------------|
| studentId | string | Yes | Filter by student ID |
| examId | string | Yes | Filter by exam ID |

#### Example Request
```bash
curl -X GET "https://api.analytics.com/v1/examInfo/20719437/exam1" \
  -H "Authorization: Bearer your-token" \
  -H "Content-Type: application/json"
```

#### Example Response
```json
{
  "data": [
    {
    "studentId": "20719437",
    "examId": "exam1";
    "totalDuration": 3509.3;
    "flaggedCount": 3;
    "questions": [
        {
          "studentId": "20719437",
          "examId": "exam1";
          "questionId": "1";
          "questionType": "essay";
          "topicId": "Heat";
          "answer": "The temperature is decreasing by 20%.";
          "answerChangeCount": 2;
          "flagged": true;
        },
        {
          "studentId": "20719437",
          "examId": "exam1";
          "questionId": "2";
          "questionType": "essay";
          "topicId": "Wavelength";
          "answer": "The sound is traversing at 350 km/h.";
          "answerChangeCount": 0;
          "flagged": false;
        }
      ];
    }
  ],
  "success": true,
  "message": "Exam information retrieved successfully"
}
```

#### Response Codes
- `200` - Success
- `400` - Bad Request
- `401` - Unauthorized
- `404` - Student or exam not found
- `500` - Internal Server Error

